# Finding 009
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; UI formatting helper duplication
- File + line(s): `packages/billing/billing-plan-client-element/src/shared/BillingPlanClientElement.vue:331-359`, `packages/billing/billing-commerce-client-element/src/shared/BillingCommerceClientElement.vue:354-385`
- Why it can drift/fail: The same fallback date and money formatting helpers are duplicated in multiple billing client elements. This copy-paste pattern makes it easy for formatting behavior to diverge between related UIs.
- Concrete impact: Inconsistent formatting rules (currency, locale fallback) between billing screens and higher maintenance cost for changes.
- Exact remediation: Extract shared formatting helpers into a common client-element utility module (e.g., `@jskit-ai/billing-client-element-core/formatters`) and reuse across billing UI components.
